Question Text:
Examine the following show command output on a router configured for dynamic NAT:
"â€” Inside Source
access-list 1 pool examsdigest
pool examsdigest: netmask 255.255.255.240
start 190.1.1.1 end 190.1.1.10
type generic, total addresses 10, allocated 10 (100%), misses 595"
You are responsible to find out why users are not being able to reach the Internet.
Choices:
a. The cause is not related to dynamic NAT
b. The command output does not provide any clue to identify the problem
c. Dynamic NAT can't use Standard ACLs
d. The NAT pool does not have enough entries to fulfill the user's requests
LLM Explanation: The correct answer is D. The output shows that the NAT pool has a total of 10 addresses, all of which are already allocated (100% allocated). Since the NAT pool is fully allocated, new users trying to reach the Internet will not be able to do so because there are no more available addresses in the pool to NAT their traffic.

Question Text: Log messages may tell you about some events, either critical or not. To help you make sense of the importance of each message, IOS assigns each message a severity level. Which of the following severity level means Warning - Warning condition?
LLM Explanation: Severity level 3 corresponds to Warning - Warning condition. It signifies a condition that is not an error, but might need special handling.

Question Text: Log messages may tell you about some events, either critical or not. To help you make sense of the importance of each message, IOS assigns each message a severity level. Which of the following severity level means Informational: Informational message only?
LLM Explanation: Severity level 4 means Informational: Informational message only in IOS. This level is purely informational and requires no action.

Question Text: One of the features of SNMPv3 is called message integrity.
LLM Explanation: The statement is TRUE. SNMPv3 provides message integrity through the use of HMAC-SHA-1 authentication. This feature ensures that the messages have not been tampered with during transmission.

Question Text: You have been tasked to find out whether the Cisco Discovery Protocol (CDP) is enabled globally. Which command will you type?
Choices:
a. show protocols
b. show cdp
c. show running-config
d. show interface brief
LLM Explanation: The correct command to determine if Cisco Discovery Protocol (CDP) is enabled globally is 'show cdp'. This command will display the CDP information, including whether it is globally enabled or disabled.

Question Text: Which of the following protocols synchronize the time of different systems?
Choices:
a. NTP
b. SMTP
c. UDP
d. CDP
LLM Explanation: NTP (Network Time Protocol) is used to synchronize the time of different systems within a network. It ensures that all devices are operating on the same time reference for various network operations and security reasons.

Question Text: R1 and R2 are attached to the same Ethernet VLAN, with subnet 192.168.1.0/24, and addresses 192.168.1.1, 192.168.2 respectively. The routers use an FHRP. Host A and host B attach to the same LAN and have correct default router settings per the FHRP configuration. Which of the following statements is true for this LAN?
Choices:
a. You can't connect two routers to the same LAN subnet.
b. If one router fails, hosts can't send packets off-subnet
c. If one router fails, both hosts will use the one remaining router as a default router
d. if one router fails, only one of the two hosts will still be able to send packets off-subnet
LLM Explanation: Option C is correct. In this scenario where R1 and R2 are attached to the same Ethernet VLAN with an FHRP (First Hop Redundancy Protocol) configured, such as HSRP or VRRP, if one router fails, both hosts will use the one remaining router as the default gateway. FHRP ensures redundancy by providing a virtual IP address shared between the routers, allowing seamless failover in case one router becomes unavailable.

Question Text: Which of the following characteristics of network traffic can be managed by Quality of Service (QoS)? (Choose all that apply)
Choices:
a. Bandwidth
b. LLQ
c. Loss
d. Delay
e. CoS
f. Jitter
LLM Explanation: Quality of Service (QoS) allows for the management of various characteristics of network traffic to ensure better performance and meet specific requirements. Bandwidth allocation, Low Latency Queuing (LLQ) for prioritizing delay-sensitive traffic, managing loss, controlling delay, Class of Service (CoS) for packet classification and marking, and handling jitter (variation in packet delay) are all aspects that can be managed using QoS mechanisms.
